Pre-Game Insights: Libya are set to feature in their 11th AFCON qualifying campaign this year, but have only reached the main draw three times, with the last being in the 2011-12 tournament.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The two nations have faced each other a total of eight times over the years and Libya hold the advantage in the head-to-head standings with five wins, while Rwanda have won once and two games finished level.
Others: Libya will be aiming to improve their performances under new management, while Rwanda will be looking to make a major improvement in this qualifying campaign after finishing rock bottom in the last edition.
